    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "From what I have found - using ArrayBuffer as the underlying object is the most consistent way to use bytes in Javascript. You then use either DataView or the TypedArrays to create and manipulate the ArrayBuffer.\r\n\r\nhttps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/ArrayBuffer\r\nhttps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/TypedArray\r\n\r\nFor example, this would give you 1 byte with all zeros in the buffer:\r\n```\r\nlet view = new DataView(new ArrayBuffer(1))\r\nview.setUint8(0, 0)\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
